Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.49,0:00:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the lectures with the same realization, the same statement about reality. Can you still hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.46,0:01:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Certain spiritual information in and of itself is transformational. To have merely
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.32,0:01:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,heard it already leaps one ahead in one's understanding of reality. And so I always
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.81,0:01:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,start with something to help us jump the whole level of the 400s, which is such a big block to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.26,0:01:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the average spiritual seeker. So we begin with the observation that nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.78,0:01:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The theory of causation calibrates around 460. It's central to the scientific paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.23,0:02:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's central to the Newtonian paradigm of reality. But enlightenment doesn't happen in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.15,0:02:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm of reality. It happens when you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.18,0:02:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens when you transcend it. I do have a bad throat, don't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.43,0:02:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We call 9-11 and they're sending somebody. They'll be here in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.56,0:02:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything. Everything is what it is of its own self, of its own self.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.18,0:02:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because each thing is coming out of creation at this moment, being what? It's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.12,0:03:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,full of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.86,0:03:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fulfilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.62,0:03:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fulfilling its karmic potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.86,0:03:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The only question that's raised here today is do I know anything about reality
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.84,0:03:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all along the history of God's creation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.33,0:03:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to build your own reflection from the movies of education,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.15,0:03:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,even might be a Spritzer programme,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.21,0:03:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I have pressure on my memory around my head and voice as much as I can,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.00,0:03:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It consists of not only years in a up and down process,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.33,0:03:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but it also consists of ten years with the transcendent of it everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.65,0:03:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the conditions are appropriate,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it fulfills its potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.86,0:03:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So this petal is not causing this petal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.52,0:03:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This stem is not causing the flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.63,0:03:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The roots are not causing, nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.87,0:03:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we witness is everything fulfilling its destiny,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.93,0:03:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,its karmic potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.16,0:03:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best that it can under prevailing conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.61,0:03:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, evolution and creation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.21,0:04:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.19,0:04:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What we witness is the unfolding of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.41,0:04:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from instant to instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.46,0:04:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that simple?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.17,0:04:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason it's critical is,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the other reason it's critical to know this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.56,0:04:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is because if you reverence the concept of causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.93,0:04:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what you establish then is there must be an I causing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.01,0:04:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.39,0:04:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you create the duality of a personal separate I
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.63,0:04:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from the infinite reality of the presence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.01,0:04:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, causality firmly then establishes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a duality in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.81,0:05:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are somewhat naive will remark
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.19,0:05:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that the doctor is channeling something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.39,0:05:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he does great channeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.56,0:05:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That comes from that same idea of duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.18,0:05:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, channeling is in duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.95,0:05:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There would be an entity on the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.06,0:05:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,like whispering in my ear,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.80,0:05:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there's a me that hears that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.43,0:05:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and announces it to you, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.37,0:05:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That would really freak me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.70,0:05:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dave, come on, listen, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.67,0:05:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.24,0:05:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see reality, you see then
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.18,0:05:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything is merely being what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:05:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the speaker at this moment is spontaneously being
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.54,0:05:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is, speaking for the knowingness within,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.67,0:06:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a presence which is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.30,0:06:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I can ask questions all day, I don't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.67,0:06:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So each thing stands forth to the fullest extent
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.02,0:06:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that it can be what it is at that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.74,0:06:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We may see it as limitation, but that's our perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.57,0:06:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being as good as it can be at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.57,0:06:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we would say it's being bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.99,0:06:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You take the package and you can't open it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you get angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.75,0:06:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are now packaged to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.42,0:06:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't get them open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.87,0:06:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to get them open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.72,0:06:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I struggle, I try.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:07:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So each thing is being what it can be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.81,0:07:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to the greatest extent it can be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to calibrate something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.00,0:07:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind is 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.04,0:07:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,505, 506, 508. My god, that's some dog. We ran into a wonderful loving dog in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,corner there who looked up at me and says, I'm over 500. Turned out he's 505.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually a dog's wagging tail is right at 500 or a kitty spur. I said, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.06,0:07:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,something about that dog, 505. The fastest way to discover the intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.17,0:07:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,reality of that which you are and the true nature of the universe is through
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.98,0:07:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,reverence. Through reverence for all of life, however it may appear to us at the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.88,0:08:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,moment. Each thing is being the best it can. You watch a videotape of a bank
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.76,0:08:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,robber and you see he's got his mask on and he's waving his gun. I mean he's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,being the best possible bank robber he can be at the moment. He's doing a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.50,0:08:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,magnificent job. I mean some of them should be on Broadway. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,fantastic. He's acting out some fantasies, some positionality, and so it's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.17,0:08:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,irrelevant to say whether what he's doing is good or bad. Good or bad has
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.84,0:08:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing to do with it. Somebody's got a gun in your head, let's not worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.50,0:08:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,good or bad. You see that mostly what
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you're doing is good or bad. You see that mostly what you're doing is good or bad. You see that mostly what
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.12,0:08:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind says about things is a luxury and when you're seeking enlightenment you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:09:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,have to forego the luxury of constant commentary on life and evaluation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.74,0:09:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,righting and wronging it, trying to decide whether God is a liberal or
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,conservative. So we have some interesting new things today. We always have
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.07,0:09:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,new things, but I don't want to shock people too much with too many new things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.79,0:09:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to eyes? All right, so let's do eyes. I was going to do movies today
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.35,0:09:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I decided to do eyes. We did 150 movies at the end of which Susan couldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.95,0:09:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,lift her right arm for about a week. Devotional non-duality means devotion to truth, devotion to vintage,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.29,0:10:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to divinity as it reveals itself by truth. It means to witness the sacredness of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.79,0:10:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you treat all of life with reverence and witness the sacredness of all of life, you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.13,0:10:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will soon identify yourself as the field and not the content of the field. Formally the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.75,0:10:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,project is to transcend the ego and one's identification with it. So I thought you'd
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.85,0:10:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,like some new research we've done and we'll verify it this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.49,0:10:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're speaking out of the other side of my mouth now? Yes. I'll speak out of the other side of my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.03,0:11:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to be good enough the way I am. I'll have to look into that. We said that, we say all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.73,0:11:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that at all times the majority of the mind is actually silent. And so if we calibrate if that's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.41,0:11:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,true, let's calibrate if that is true. At all times ninety-eight percent of the mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.37,0:11:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What we hear is the clatter of one or two percent. Ninety-eight percent of your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.76,0:11:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is silent at all times. So why complain about it? You're only talking about two percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.09,0:12:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well that cuts down the project, doesn't it? I just saved you ninety-eight percent of what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.00,0:12:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you thought you were going to have to do. You're welcome. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.30,0:12:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So why does the, why does the remaining two percent seem to be such a problem? And we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.37,0:12:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered it's because you are in a hypnotic state, hypnotized by that two percent. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.33,0:12:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You are in a trance. Resist. Everybody is in a hypnotic trance at the effect. You've
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.23,0:12:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,become the prisoner through hypnosis of that two percent. You've become entranced with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.67,0:13:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it, fascinated with it, and now you've let two percent of your mind run all of you. And
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.52,0:13:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not a good investment. Ninety-eight percent then would reveal the true nature
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.86,0:13:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality. So when I say try to find the silent part of your mind, first of all you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.39,0:13:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,have to know it exists. Right at this moment, right before you just had that last thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.28,0:13:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind was silent. Yep, and now it's silent again. And now it's silent again. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.48,0:13:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a little word goes across.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.00,0:13:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypnotic state. One can pray to God to relieve you and return you to sanity from being at
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.70,0:14:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect of hypnosis, a hypnotic trance from the content of one's mind, and pray for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.50,0:14:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,liberation. Liberation means to be liberated from the illusion that you are the two percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.42,0:14:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see where the two percent gets its juice from. Huh. If nonduality is, you know, the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.63,0:14:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,state of enlightenment, then duality would be the state one wishes to transcend. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.95,0:14:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,found the way through the eyes. The I-Z-E of life. We polarize, stems from the process
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.33,0:14:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're going to call eyes. This two percent eyes-es you all the time. And how does it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.50,0:15:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes you? Well, you'll see. When it looks at something out there, it has the habit of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.66,0:15:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,politicizing it. Everywhere I speak, everybody asks me to do George Bush. What do they think
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.14,0:15:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to come out? Ninety-two or something? Not the same as Roosevelt, Truman, the same
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.96,0:15:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as every other president. Okay, so we ask, is God a liberal? We go, no, he's not. The
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.62,0:15:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha said, wisdom is the middle way. Okay. All right. Because either extreme is insanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,right? So politicize then causes dissension and conversation in your mind. You read the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.62,0:15:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,paper, you argue with the news, you argue with the editorial writer. So to politicize
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.77,0:15:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is instantly to create a duality and create conflict. That's one of the great enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:16:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of peace. The next great enemy of peace is to moralize. So if we politicize and moralize,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.60,0:16:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which is everybody's habit when they read the paper or watch the news, you can see why
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.24,0:16:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is divided into good or bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.14,0:16:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Moralize. What if you didn't moralize? What if you were just the witness? Let's say you're
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.37,0:16:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from another planet, another galaxy, and you're here to witness the phenomena in this place
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.12,0:16:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and report back, but all you can say is things seem to be happening. Things go up, things
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.75,0:16:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,go down, things live, they fall over, something is born, they clap or they cry, depending
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.35,0:16:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,on the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.35,0:16:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.50,0:16:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When it passes out of existence and they call it dying,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.33,0:17:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,people clap or cry depending on the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.13,0:17:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to see that one go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The best thing he did for mankind is pass on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.65,0:17:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you say it shouldn't be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.26,0:17:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.59,0:17:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The best way to politicize is to moralize and idealize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.07,0:17:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you get on a soapbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.38,0:17:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the soapbox eyes, a great trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.70,0:17:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get your ankle in it, it's very hard to get it out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.38,0:17:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because any way you move, you trigger another response.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.11,0:17:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you're in duality, every move triggers a response.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you decide you're wrong and back up,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.93,0:17:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you will now be attacked for changing your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.15,0:17:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and backing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.64,0:17:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you don't, you'd be criticized
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.05,0:17:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for not having done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.96,0:17:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a no-win situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.94,0:17:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.24,0:18:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you get into duality, you cannot win.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.38,0:18:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you win, you will get punished, highly taxed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.85,0:18:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and criticized.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.34,0:18:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe be bombed and assassinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.07,0:18:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the explanation for 9-11?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.53,0:18:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Americans work hard, save their money,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.29,0:18:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to live an integrous life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.24,0:18:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That made them hate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.14,0:18:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because America had wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get wealth?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.41,0:18:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You work your butt off, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.24,0:18:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.74,0:18:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're political.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.98,0:18:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're politicized and moralized and then idealized,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.81,0:18:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you've set up the next war.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.43,0:18:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the basis of war right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.55,0:18:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,War has nothing to do with guns, munitions, bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.19,0:18:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are just the aftermath, the mechanics of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.58,0:18:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Once two guys decide how they're going to kill each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.84,0:18:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't make any difference whether you use swords, guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.30,0:18:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the weaponry is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking around for weaponry is a real waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.53,0:19:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I worry about this guy, I'll have to search through his 10
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.57,0:19:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and see if he's got a dagger in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.33,0:19:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I want to worry about whether he's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,got a dagger in there, because I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.61,0:19:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,reading where this guy's at, and he's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,going to get me one way or the other, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.65,0:19:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.15,0:19:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So we politicize, we moralize, we idealize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.90,0:19:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is how we set up war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what war comes out of, the first three items.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.96,0:19:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then out of that, we speculate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.42,0:19:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we begin to hypothesize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.38,0:19:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be this way, it could be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.17,0:19:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,People ask you the hypothetical question, but what if?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.29,0:19:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Never answer what if.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.14,0:19:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two questions you never answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.11,0:19:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One is why, and the other is what if.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.69,0:19:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the bear traps, all set for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.74,0:19:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute somebody says what if, you know they're out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:20:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to get you in their bear trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.64,0:20:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What if?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.22,0:20:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.94,0:20:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if everybody ate an ice cream cone
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time on the planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.44,0:20:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that cause a shortage of, I mean, you know what I
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.90,0:20:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical has absolutely no grounding in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.55,0:20:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical is the grossly distorted pseudo-scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.40,0:20:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,studies that prove that this is dangerous, or that's dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or this is dangerous, and keeps everybody frightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.57,0:20:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and programs everybody with negative programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.26,0:20:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't so before, everybody's believing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes it happen now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.22,0:20:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, you've done the course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.64,0:20:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're subject to that which you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.01,0:20:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you think this is going to kill you, it's going to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.82,0:20:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, there's no way around it anyway, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.72,0:21:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because statistics show more people who ride in the passenger seat die than in the rear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.08,0:21:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,seat, therefore you better not sit in the passenger seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.36,0:21:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,However, more people who sit on the right-hand side in the passenger back seat die than on
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.41,0:21:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't sit on the right side either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.33,0:21:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,More people who park on highways get killed on the highway than park in parking lots.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.38,0:21:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,lot so you can't park in there. You get what I'm saying? More people die in the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.98,0:21:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,bathroom than die in the kitchen so you can't go in the bathroom. Then you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.24,0:21:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,gotta go to the bathroom and then you find out more people get killed in the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.07,0:21:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,kitchen than do in the bedroom. You got to stay in the bedroom. More people get
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.77,0:21:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,killed coming down from the second floor bedroom than the first floor bedroom so
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.20,0:21:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see how if you're gonna run your life by hypothetical
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.94,0:21:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,statistics it gets really awkward, you know what I'm saying? The best thing to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.09,0:21:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,live your life as you see it this way you can and you remember from previous
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.49,0:21:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,research that the time of your death is already preset so there's no trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.04,0:22:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,no point trying to doubt guess God. Karmically the time is determined at the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.72,0:22:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,moment you are born. We reaffirm that is a fact the Lord. That is a fact we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.20,0:22:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,reaffirmed in every lecture. You don't have to worry about death because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.85,0:22:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,already taken care of. The other thing you have to worry about is you're never
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.49,0:22:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,going to experience your own death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.49,0:22:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway it's not possible. The instant of death, bang, you're out of the body, you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.15,0:22:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,witness it, you feel sorry for the people there but you're fine. I should have done
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.59,0:22:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this a long time ago, comes to you. That motorcycle accident, I should have said
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.84,0:22:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to hell with the respirator and anyway. So you see the karmic unfoldment then of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.90,0:22:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality. Karma then is, you're not controlled by karma but it does set up
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.25,0:22:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.38,0:23:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say extreme guilt over something you've done in some lifetime gets you left
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.27,0:23:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in a hot car, a little toddler with the windows closed and after an hour you're dead. Everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.80,0:23:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sentimentalizes about that. Oh poor little tyke. If you look at poor little tyke in a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.81,0:23:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,previous lifetime you won't think it's poor little tyke. What is the karmic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.09,0:23:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.11,0:23:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,See either everything is happening by accident which would negate the possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.81,0:23:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity or nothing is happening by accident because accidents are not possible. An accident
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.40,0:23:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,really denotes an intellectual limitation. What it means is you don't understand the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.66,0:24:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons for it. In the infinite power of divinity no such thing as an accident is possible. This
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.94,0:24:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,comes around.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.57,0:24:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Here swoops down there and in my own lifetime having gone through extreme agony out of a karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.25,0:24:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,obligation which I've already told you about, the recall of the reason for what I was going
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.70,0:24:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,through was clear as a bell. You remembered the extreme guilt about not having killed that guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.79,0:24:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,not having killed him. The warrior I wounded in the groin and left him to die of the wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.79,0:24:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have put him to sleep and didn't though. I was in linha infirmum and brought
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.07,0:24:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a herniography with no anesthesia once I햇rproud. Which wouldn't recommend unless you have
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.22,0:24:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,gored someone to death and still feel guilty about it. In this case you will have undone
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.48,0:25:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that guilt by the time you're through.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.59,0:25:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity means that one can grab sort of the overall context, divinity field out of which
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.34,0:25:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,universe happens with
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.65,0:25:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,within it is evolving. The quickest way to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.48,0:25:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is to look over great expanses of time. Look over great expanses
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.74,0:25:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of time. Don't look at just this little thing. But that this little thing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.38,0:25:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is happening, you know, in a progression of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.24,0:25:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,time that runs millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.16,0:25:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we hypothesize
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.60,0:25:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of hypothesis
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.00,0:26:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we get all kinds of fallacious answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.68,0:26:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing we do is we romanticize. We romanticize
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.64,0:26:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about all kinds of things and create a flowery
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.75,0:26:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,imagination of how it could be, should be,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.70,0:26:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and then become dissatisfied if
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.21,0:26:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it does not compare favorably with our
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.67,0:26:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,romanticization of it. So to romanticize
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.36,0:26:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.67,0:26:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what we do is to project onto it. So all these
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.74,0:26:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,examples you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.05,0:26:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,something is happening out there, and then the mind projects this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.90,0:26:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,interpretation
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.85,0:26:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,onto it. Then believes that what it just projected onto the world is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.35,0:26:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.16,0:26:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So through this little example, you'll quickly see
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.25,0:26:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that any commentary you can make about life is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.25,0:26:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,always a projection. Because when you experience a rejection,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.94,0:27:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing to say about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.48,0:27:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to say about it. It just is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.00,0:27:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So to romanticize, then, is to set oneself up for fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.24,0:27:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To elaborate, where no elaboration is really necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.24,0:27:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It means to exaggerate certain qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.55,0:27:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To romanticize, you have to distort it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.92,0:27:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As compared to romanticizing, you have to distort it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.24,0:27:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,To romanticize, there's reverence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.49,0:27:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's reverence for the beauty of a relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.75,0:27:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's reverence for the intrinsic innocence of the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.91,0:27:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to romanticize it, which
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.97,0:27:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,means to distort and to exaggerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.39,0:28:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The next one is rather obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.44,0:28:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, it follows from the previous ones. To criticize,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.47,0:28:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, is,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.17,0:28:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is a rather glaring, obvious ego function.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.25,0:28:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This should be that. They shouldn't have done this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.25,0:28:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They should have done this. They shouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.25,0:28:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can look at the black beetle laying on his back,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.25,0:28:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,his little legs wanging around in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.25,0:28:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, you shouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.25,0:28:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have looked where you're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.25,0:28:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't have walked...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.35,0:28:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see how absurd criticize is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.35,0:28:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So at the end, we're going to give you a little mnemonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.82,0:28:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The fastest way to God is to become aware of the eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.82,0:28:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that your mind is eysing out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.85,0:28:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby become wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.30,0:28:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.98,0:29:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So the progression through the ego is primarily one of self-observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.35,0:29:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And many teachers, you know, say the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.35,0:29:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was Mr. Gadara Maharaj.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.80,0:29:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They would tell the students, watch the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.80,0:29:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.40,0:29:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if that worked or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.40,0:29:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.20,0:29:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to define in what way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.51,0:29:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch how it begins to criticize,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.19,0:29:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and you watch how it begins to emotionalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.85,0:29:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,See, first it politicizes, then it moralizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.85,0:29:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,then it idealizes, then it hypothesizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.85,0:29:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,then it romanticizes, then it criticizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.90,0:29:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it goes into indignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.90,0:29:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.90,0:29:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Or oo-ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.90,0:29:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sentimentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.40,0:29:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sentimentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.40,0:29:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor baby in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.61,0:29:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Wah, wah, wah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.86,0:30:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Cries over everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.86,0:30:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it's indignant over everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.86,0:30:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees everything as tragedy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.01,0:30:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or something that needs to be corrected.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.01,0:30:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And who should correct what is criticized?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.33,0:30:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Who should do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.50,0:30:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.06,0:30:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You should take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.06,0:30:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And how are you going to take care of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.06,0:30:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to take care of it by telling the people
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.06,0:30:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,who are wrong how wrong they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.02,0:30:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And how they should have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.22,0:30:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody tries that with their spouse, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.22,0:30:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the children, your mother-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.22,0:30:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know he doesn't like blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.01,0:30:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you bought him the blue shirts.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.18,0:30:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So we emotionalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.47,0:30:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalize is another form of exaggeration.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.88,0:30:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalizing is exaggerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.77,0:30:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalizing is a way to dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.77,0:31:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.04,0:31:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're connected with reality, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.00,0:31:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody says, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.00,0:31:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you're probably going to die of this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.17,0:31:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in a couple of days or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.17,0:31:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good. Glad you told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.05,0:31:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call and shut the phone off
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.05,0:31:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell them to hold the mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.25,0:31:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.27,0:31:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's to emotionalize about?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.92,0:31:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to emotionalize because you want to dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.92,0:31:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.54,0:31:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So emotionalizing is trying to make things bigger than they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.68,0:31:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I see somebody in the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.68,0:31:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's all broken down and crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.68,0:31:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's carrying on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.68,0:31:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, what's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.85,0:31:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother-in-law is having her gallbladder out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.47,0:31:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, help me God.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.47,0:31:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.59,0:31:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is she blubbering all over the place
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.59,0:32:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's her mother-in-law having her gallbladder out?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.05,0:32:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the poor boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.05,0:32:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The poor boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.29,0:32:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog is sick, so you're depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.29,0:32:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The bird gets hit by the windshield of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.29,0:32:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.68,0:32:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you're the windshield.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.68,0:32:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you're the bug, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.48,0:32:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened just recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.48,0:32:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Driving along at high speed and all of a sudden a bird flew right into the windshield.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.50,0:32:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye-bye birdie.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.09,0:32:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The only concern was that she would be upset by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.90,0:32:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it is shocking if you run over an animal by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.33,0:32:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody who's done it knows it's sort of a horrible feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.33,0:32:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we see that the mind, the 2% then,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.07,0:32:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,how does it become so dominant?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.29,0:32:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the mechanisms by which it becomes dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.29,0:33:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's opinionated about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.69,0:33:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always right and wronging things.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.69,0:33:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That creates enemies and friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.69,0:33:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It idealizes how it should be, which of course it can't be or it would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.88,0:33:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It hypothesizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.46,0:33:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at the nature of the world we live in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.46,0:33:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and understand what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.49,0:33:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be no point to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.36,0:33:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The human world we live in is the ultimate perfect place
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.36,0:33:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for spiritual evolution, just as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.36,0:33:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is as it is because it offers the most possible alternatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.53,0:34:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It offers the greatest karmic opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.59,0:34:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost from instant to instant one can say yes or no, yes or no.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.84,0:34:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One can reverence life or despise it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.84,0:34:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One can curse or bless.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.84,0:34:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Every instant then.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.84,0:34:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the soul, I always liken it to an iron filing,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.42,0:34:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, with polarity and a charge on it and all, or a molecule.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.42,0:34:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So every moment this little molecule is saying yes to this, no to this,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.03,0:34:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,yes to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.03,0:34:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night the story of the ocean depths was on.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.03,0:34:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a stunningly beautiful thing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.03,0:34:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you see these incredible things floating through the air like this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.42,0:34:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's long.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.42,0:34:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the same time it's luminescent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.57,0:34:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's incredible beauty, incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.57,0:34:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.61,0:34:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When you don't project criticism, romanticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.61,0:35:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when you just witness these little, smaller than protozoa or whatever they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.92,0:35:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't get the name of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.92,0:35:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Their beauty was too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.92,0:35:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to call them anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.44,0:35:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And like little umbrellas that go like this, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.50,0:35:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just entrancing, magnificently, incredibly beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.50,0:35:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple thousand feet below the sea is a world of incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.78,0:35:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also, and they also eat each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.51,0:35:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that awful?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.38,0:35:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because if you don't get eaten, you don't get to evolve into something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.38,0:35:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody doesn't eat the cow, the cow's spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.38,0:35:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,how will it birth itself as a living entity in a world of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.50,0:35:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If everybody becomes a vegetarian, what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.90,0:35:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill all the cattle, let them die of old age, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.82,0:36:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of cattle won't be out there going moo.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.82,0:36:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to the girl's ranch in the morning, I pass through a herd of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.09,0:36:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll stop and say hello to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.09,0:36:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They stand there and look at you, go on by, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.09,0:36:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also have to stop and greet them and tell them good morning, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.32,0:36:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell them, if it wasn't for McDonald's, you wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.46,0:36:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you don't do all of this, then you can just love the cow
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.07,0:36:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that somehow its spirit evolved by being of service,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.17,0:36:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by laying down its life for some kind of a higher creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.17,0:36:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And somehow, because the evolution of consciousness then proceeds
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.71,0:36:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,over vast amounts of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.75,0:37:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and expresses itself in a great multitude of life forms,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.88,0:37:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course when we calibrate the energy fields of living things
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.17,0:37:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,starting maybe 400 million years ago and coming on up,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.17,0:37:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that consciousness is evolving.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.17,0:37:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some horse has got to become a cow, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.17,0:37:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to become a mammalian, which births,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.40,0:37:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which then releases the maternal,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.42,0:37:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which begins to express love and nurturance.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.59,0:37:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see love and nurturance in the dragon family.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.65,0:37:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be a cow, you've got to be a sheep,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.71,0:37:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to be a bird, care about the egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.13,0:37:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere in evolution you've got to come out of the reptilian,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.13,0:37:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.61,0:38:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The Komodo dragon is still around, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.05,0:38:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does love birth itself on the planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.57,0:38:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do it through a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.57,0:38:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The Komodo dragon automatically kills you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.57,0:38:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't know any other way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.17,0:38:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It just bites you and it waits until you die, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.92,0:38:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's as far as it could go in evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.92,0:38:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see a Komodo dragon becoming a warm mother cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.71,0:38:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it stays a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.71,0:38:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Something else comes off and evolves and evolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.63,0:38:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The world as we see it is perfect, perfect, perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.01,0:38:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.38,0:38:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the world that you bemoan is all a projection.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.86,0:38:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it too bad? Isn't that sad? Shouldn't that be better?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.86,0:38:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see those are all mentations?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.13,0:38:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All mentations, those are all mentations.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.71,0:39:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stop the mentations, you merely witness it as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.03,0:39:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So we like to emotionalize and dramatize
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.03,0:39:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and in doing that we exaggerate
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.03,0:39:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and now everything becomes a catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.28,0:39:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Catastrophize.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.82,0:39:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is a catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.69,0:39:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The newspapers specialize in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.94,0:39:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The news channels love catastrophes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.94,0:39:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't get to a big accident fast enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.26,0:39:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourteen people killed on a so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.26,0:39:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, the helicopters are right out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.26,0:39:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just sucking up the drama of the catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.26,0:39:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Grinding it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.59,0:39:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.30,0:39:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So to exaggerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.30,0:39:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Say your mother-in-law is having her gallbladder out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.30,0:39:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.30,0:39:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not going to do it while she's awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.50,0:39:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She's going to have Demerol afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.50,0:39:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She's going to have sterile fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.50,0:39:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She's going to have stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.57,0:39:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Our great-grandmothers didn't have,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.57,0:39:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or my grandmother didn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.57,0:39:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They were lucky if they survived surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.57,0:40:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky if they survived surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.53,0:40:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She's going to have anesthesia, which is more than I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.57,0:40:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So we catastrophize and we dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.57,0:40:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We say this world should be a different world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.11,0:40:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And we begin to theorize about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.69,0:40:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how we're going to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.69,0:40:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the new direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.82,0:40:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And we theorize.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.11,0:40:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And universities are great at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.11,0:40:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.42,0:40:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We just calibrated all the universities last weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.42,0:40:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.42,0:40:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Big Ten, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.42,0:40:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Come out really about the highest.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.42,0:40:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.80,0:40:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Ten universities.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.80,0:40:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Come out higher than the Ivy League.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.80,0:40:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.21,0:40:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.53,0:40:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we begin to theorize about how we could
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.69,0:40:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,solve men's problems, what we conceive as problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.69,0:40:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, because there isn't a problem there,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.69,0:40:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or any solution that you can come up with
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.78,0:40:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.78,0:41:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,coerce the world into following is going to be disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.78,0:41:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.78,0:41:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You have all these isms, which are all hypothetical solutions
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.78,0:41:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to hypothetical problems which don't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.78,0:41:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All you can say is in every barrel of apples,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.17,0:41:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,some apples are going to be near the top
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.17,0:41:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and some are going to be near the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.38,0:41:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.38,0:41:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, well, it shouldn't be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.44,0:41:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All children should be able to run as fast as others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.92,0:41:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it should be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.92,0:41:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus it in that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.34,0:41:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I only got one F in my life, and that was in sports.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.19,0:41:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to bring my 50 cents or my towel card
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.73,0:41:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for the semester, and I got flunked.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.92,0:41:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And they used to have what they call field day.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.23,0:41:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That to me was horror day.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.23,0:42:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to try and think up a headache or a sick stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.19,0:42:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're going to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.19,0:42:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things you had to do in sports day
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.25,0:42:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is they would have a rope from the ceiling of the gymnasium,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.25,0:42:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and you would have to climb this freaking rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.07,0:42:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Second.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.07,0:42:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I never got past the middle of the rope much to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.48,0:42:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.84,0:42:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, mesomorphs are going up there like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.96,0:42:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not fair that I wasn't born a mesomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.01,0:42:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a young gentleman here who I love dearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.09,0:42:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a great fan of ours, and he is a mesomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.09,0:42:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time I hug him, I say, God, that's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.09,0:42:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy can probably lift a safe or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.15,0:42:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.15,0:42:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm having trouble opening a package of light bulbs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.15,0:42:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from the dime store.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.15,0:42:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get through the plastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.15,0:42:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.38,0:43:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently we did a recording for a big company,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.07,0:43:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the people that came from the company,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.07,0:43:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the vice president of the company, was 6'6".
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.53,0:43:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking up at him like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.53,0:43:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.23,0:43:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the fun things about being in Korea is the average height there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.26,0:43:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The average height there is much less than here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.32,0:43:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I was in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.32,0:43:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to feel what it's like to be a tall guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.61,0:43:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's head's about this high.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.61,0:43:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you feel like Mr. Big.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.26,0:43:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.98,0:43:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypothesize. Is that fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.98,0:43:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.98,0:43:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've got a political solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.98,0:44:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's going to get chopped off at the same level.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.84,0:44:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bantus and the Watusi, so help me God, did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.46,0:44:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Historical fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.46,0:44:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bantus cut the Watusi's legs off in their war.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.61,0:44:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're all the same size.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.38,0:44:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's catastrophizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.07,0:44:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of that we theorize wondrous solutions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.13,0:44:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do that by intellectualizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.13,0:44:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, rationalize is making excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.13,0:44:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody knows that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.46,0:44:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things that we're talking about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.46,0:44:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if you witness your mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.46,0:44:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see it's doing one or the other of these things all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.50,0:44:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't hold you in thralldom.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.50,0:44:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,By being stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.09,0:44:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It has fascinating dilemmas, fascinating solutions,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.09,0:44:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,great dramas, great emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.30,0:44:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we rationalize our behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.57,0:44:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We rationalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.57,0:44:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a three-year-old.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.57,0:45:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You say to the three-year-old,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.57,0:45:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,did you knock that over?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.26,0:45:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't do it, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.26,0:45:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.28,0:45:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.28,0:45:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the world of excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.42,0:45:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuses are a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.42,0:45:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But it satisfies the three-year-old in us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.42,0:45:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we've created such an impossible dilemma for ourself now,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.09,0:45:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we need relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.53,0:45:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's called fantasize.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.53,0:45:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You go to the movies, you read the novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.55,0:45:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We daydream and we fantasize
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.78,0:45:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because we've made life so painful and unrewarding
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.90,0:45:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that we now have to create an imaginary world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.90,0:45:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Where things are more dramatic, more right,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.90,0:45:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,more the way we want them to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.90,0:46:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We fantasize about how it should be, could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.73,0:46:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing we tend to do is infantilize.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.73,0:46:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We infantilize people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.73,0:46:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always political solutions to non-problems
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.73,0:46:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because we've infantilized the people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.73,0:46:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and pictured that they're helpless and hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.96,0:46:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we can be the good person
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.05,0:46:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and come in and bail them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.05,0:46:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Bail them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.13,0:46:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the first step in Al-Anon
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.61,0:46:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and those types of recovery programs
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.61,0:46:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is to allow them to sink on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.73,0:46:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're going down the tubes,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.53,0:46:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,cheer them on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.13,0:46:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going down the tubes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.48,0:46:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the only way you can hit bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.65,0:46:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is by going down the tubes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.65,0:46:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you infantilize them
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.80,0:46:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and see them as helpless and hopeless
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.80,0:46:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to support them and hold them up,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.80,0:47:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you can keep them physically surviving
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.80,0:47:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,long past the endpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.80,0:47:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And their recovery then is allowing them
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.21,0:47:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to take responsibility for their own actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.21,0:47:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We rationalize and then another form of that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.25,0:47:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is called intellectualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.25,0:47:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why some of the universities
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.40,0:47:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't come out too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.40,0:47:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in the practice of medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.40,0:47:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this one is the one that really blows you away.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.69,0:47:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the massive dilemma of practicing medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.69,0:47:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is all coming out of intellectualization.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.69,0:47:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectualization.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.03,0:47:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently the government passed some new regulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.03,0:47:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which was totally, completely fraudulent,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.03,0:47:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,called the HIPAA regulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.03,0:47:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,H-I-P-P-A.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.32,0:47:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The public thinks that the privacy of their medical records
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.32,0:47:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is now being protected by these HIPAA regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.61,0:47:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, quite the contrary is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.61,0:48:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the time of Hippocrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.61,0:48:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,every doctor has guarded the privacy
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.61,0:48:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of his patient's information.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.61,0:48:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, a lot of them will go to jail
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.61,0:48:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than review it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.61,0:48:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And they have periodically.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.71,0:48:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, what they've actually done with the Privacy Act
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.71,0:48:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is make your medical records available to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.44,0:48:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Any company, anybody with a vested interest
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.44,0:48:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in your health, welfare, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.67,0:48:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,now has access to your medical records.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.73,0:48:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The great HIPAA Privacy Act was exactly the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.73,0:48:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the non-privacy act.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.73,0:48:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're not gaining privacy, you're losing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.73,0:48:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.03,0:48:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You could do all that in one sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.03,0:48:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for months and years I've been getting piles.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.65,0:48:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My HIPAA file, I am not kidding, is this thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.65,0:48:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all bulletins and issues and regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.84,0:48:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The granddaddy of them all came last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.84,0:48:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a whole notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.84,0:49:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnificent production.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.38,0:49:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I sign this and return it to the company,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.38,0:49:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they will give me a certificate saying
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.38,0:49:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm complying with the HIPAA regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.71,0:49:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They never heard of Hippocrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.94,0:49:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They never heard of the oath of Hippocrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.94,0:49:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know a single doctor that doesn't guard
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.94,0:49:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,his patients with a paranoid ferocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.23,0:49:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So that all comes out of intellectualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.23,0:49:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the one thing about intellectualize
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.30,0:49:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is the more complicated you can make it, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.38,0:49:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that Medicare regulations run 10,000 pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.51,0:49:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,10,000 pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.86,0:49:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the proliferation of complexity then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.86,0:49:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of intellectualizations
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.19,0:49:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and also, sorry, legal experience in courts.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.19,0:49:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That everything has to be documented
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.19,0:50:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to the point of absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.19,0:50:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And for some years,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.28,0:50:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the only psychiatrist that would go around
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.28,0:50:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to the nursing homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.28,0:50:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I saw zillions of old people.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.28,0:50:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And their charts were magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.28,0:50:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's this old lady who doesn't say anything
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.28,0:50:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.28,0:50:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She takes a couple pills a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.28,0:50:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And her chart is this thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.69,0:50:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Weighs 10 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.86,0:50:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time she goes to the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.05,0:50:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,asks for a glass of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.05,0:50:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has to sign for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.46,0:50:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellectualization then.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.46,0:50:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, everybody's complaining
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.46,0:50:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,about the cost of medical care.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.46,0:50:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.46,0:50:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Just remember that from the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.46,0:50:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the cost of medical care is 9% is the physician's fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.46,0:50:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is bureaucracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.46,0:50:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,9% of the total medical bill is the physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.46,0:50:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,93% comes out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.46,0:50:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of this plus what if.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.55,0:50:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what if you didn't document
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.61,0:50:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that you went to the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.94,0:51:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She might die of constipation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.05,0:51:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be sued for death by constipation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.09,0:51:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In as much as we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.09,0:51:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically, when she's supposed to leave this world
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.09,0:51:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is set already.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.21,0:51:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To even blame anybody is,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.21,0:51:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from a higher viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.21,0:51:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.21,0:51:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing causes anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.21,0:51:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing causes anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.21,0:51:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So intellectualize then means to complicate things
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.21,0:51:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so they become cumbersome and manageable,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.21,0:51:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,inefficient, and extremely costly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.21,0:51:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Extremely costly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.13,0:51:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People worry about the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.13,0:51:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of people always predicting
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.13,0:51:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of the world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.13,0:51:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a workshop somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.13,0:51:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,on the end of the world about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.53,0:51:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And people don't really know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.59,0:51:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,how the end of the world is going to come about,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.59,0:52:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.44,0:52:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A giant massive gridlock
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.59,0:52:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes so overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.59,0:52:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that finally a complete paralysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.59,0:52:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing can move any further
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.59,0:52:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because all the regulations make it so that if you...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.59,0:52:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday I was trying to get an older patient
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.05,0:52:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,into an emergency into the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.05,0:52:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in Cottonwood, Verde Valley Medical Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.23,0:52:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And the complexity of such a simple accomplishment,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.46,0:52:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.46,0:52:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's better to let them die, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.26,0:52:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.46,0:52:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Before this intellectualization
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.65,0:52:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,caused such enormous complexity,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.65,0:52:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when I had a huge practice,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.05,0:52:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd call the hospital and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.05,0:53:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,this guy's coming in, send the ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.05,0:53:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it took.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.76,0:53:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it takes me dozens of phone calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.05,0:53:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the phone for hours
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.05,0:53:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to get through the bureaucratic complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.05,0:53:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually a person could have died
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.05,0:53:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,long before you get them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.05,0:53:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.50,0:53:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything then...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.50,0:53:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You eventually hit a gridlock, a log jam,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.50,0:53:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,where effective functioning becomes almost impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.73,0:53:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And apparently that's what happened before 9-11.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.73,0:53:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The government agencies were so bogged down
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.73,0:53:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with their interfacing rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.73,0:53:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't speak to him
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.73,0:53:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you get permission from so-and-so,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.73,0:53:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's against Rule 62 and you have...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.73,0:53:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So finally it just became stultified.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.73,0:53:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All the information was there,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.73,0:53:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but nobody had, like, permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.73,0:53:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have permission to call him and tell him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.75,0:53:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.96,0:53:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.28,0:54:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So intellectualize then means eventually great complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.28,0:54:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the whole process is mentalizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.53,0:54:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say the way to enlightenment is to observe,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.63,0:54:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that your mind is constantly mentalizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.90,0:54:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What you think is out there is a mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.50,0:54:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The belief in causation, causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.50,0:54:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm, right and wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.78,0:54:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all mentalizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.78,0:54:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They only exist as the thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.78,0:54:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things that you presume exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.61,0:54:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot find in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.84,0:54:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only find them as a thought process.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.00,0:54:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no concordant reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.00,0:54:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,no concordant reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.00,0:54:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So mentalizing then is what the 2% is doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.09,0:54:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping us hypnotized by the process,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.15,0:54:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the process, the phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.50,0:55:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,all these indignations,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.50,0:55:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,moralization,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.50,0:55:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,romanticization,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.50,0:55:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,erotization.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.50,0:55:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't put that up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.50,0:55:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Erotization.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.23,0:55:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a lot of that going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.90,0:55:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And fantasize, mentalize,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.90,0:55:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.90,0:55:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we said idealize,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.90,0:55:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and it went up there twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.90,0:55:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.94,0:55:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is how it should be,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.09,0:55:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is how it should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.09,0:55:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guess how it should be must have been the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.71,0:55:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when I wrote that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.71,0:55:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how the list should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.05,0:55:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I better have idealized on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.61,0:55:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm glad I got it up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.90,0:55:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we get to another great trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.61,0:55:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one is a little harder to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.61,0:55:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something people don't realize
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.82,0:56:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,goes on all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.82,0:56:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is called glamorize.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.96,0:56:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamorize is somewhat a product of emotionalize
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.38,0:56:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and romanticize and idealize.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.38,0:56:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We glamorize phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.46,0:56:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We glamorize political positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.46,0:56:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you give this firepower
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.46,0:56:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is you glamorize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.46,0:56:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You glamorize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.00,0:56:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You give it pseudo-importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.32,0:56:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You get somebody with a big name.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.32,0:56:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You present it as a dramatic presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.53,0:56:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,with all kinds of color and a full orchestra.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.53,0:56:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever watch some nature program on television?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.53,0:56:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And while this nature program is going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.53,0:56:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all this dramatic music is going on in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.53,0:56:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hear what the announcer is talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.53,0:56:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, when they're showing an ant walking across a leaf,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.82,0:56:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,do you have to have this drama music in the background?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.82,0:56:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that ever annoy you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.82,0:57:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's drama music put in as background to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.78,0:57:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that should be incredibly of themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.13,0:57:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,overwhelmingly beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.13,0:57:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,now are brought down by what the producer thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.23,0:57:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get this drama music in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.96,0:57:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Da-dum, da-dum, da-dum, da-dum.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.96,0:57:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes just a fly going along.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.96,0:57:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's this drama music.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.96,0:57:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You would think this is the end of the world about to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.96,0:57:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dramatization, the romanticization,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.38,0:57:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then leads to a glamorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.44,0:57:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So many political positions and many ideologies
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.73,0:57:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,become glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.73,0:57:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.73,0:57:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Workers unite.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.32,0:57:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have nothing to lose but your chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.32,0:57:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, that sounds great, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.32,0:57:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't get you out to the barricades.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.34,0:57:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got no heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.63,0:57:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're out to the barricades, you've got no head.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.63,0:58:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're just going to get blown away.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.63,0:58:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly, everything's going to go back the way it was before anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.63,0:58:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you can go down as a hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.82,0:58:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's a glamorization right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.82,0:58:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,To glamorize, again, means to make it bigger than life,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.46,0:58:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to overemphasize,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.46,0:58:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to make that which is less than salutary a pure attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.69,0:58:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,M.T.V., of course, is the stunning ultimate example of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.98,0:58:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And various video games.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.98,0:58:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Some video games are so incredibly non-integrist
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.98,0:58:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that I don't want to even describe what they're about.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.36,0:58:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, nobody would produce anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.36,0:58:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor would anybody buy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.36,0:58:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you find it's the biggest seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.78,0:58:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.78,0:58:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The glamorization of that which the world calls evil, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.46,0:58:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is glamorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.46,0:58:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It, of course, fills up the TV channels every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.46,0:59:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The glamorization of all the criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.46,0:59:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonnie and Clyde,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.50,0:59:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they become romanticized and glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.50,0:59:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they're attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.82,0:59:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, how do these young kids all get into lives of crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.82,0:59:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they want to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.88,0:59:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.88,0:59:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You wear your hat this way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.42,0:59:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You collect all the symbols, the gang symbols.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.42,0:59:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You be Mr. Tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.73,0:59:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.73,0:59:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Make big money doing drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.84,0:59:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very glamorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.94,0:59:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of glamor is that it is something sprayed onto life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.34,0:59:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to make it look attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.34,0:59:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you take that away, you see it's quite ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.34,0:59:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.34,0:59:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.55,0:59:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing the mind does is demonize everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.55,0:59:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to do that out of politicize, moralize, and idealize.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.75,0:59:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing it does is want to demonize.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.75,1:00:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said the way around that is to catch your mind at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.61,1:00:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you're pro-vanilla,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.19,1:00:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't mean you have to kill chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.19,1:00:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to get up the barricades and the machine guns.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.30,1:00:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to assassinate chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.09,1:00:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate chocolate clubs.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.13,1:00:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can declare chocolate is un-American.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.13,1:00:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not fair to the great masses.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.86,1:00:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's elitism.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.86,1:00:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's elitist.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.46,1:00:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Vanilla is the flavor of the masses.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.09,1:00:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And chocolate is the fete elite.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.09,1:00:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we can demonize anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.82,1:00:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we know that everything is bad for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.61,1:00:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think something is not bad for you, it's because you haven't heard yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.38,1:01:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is fatal.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.38,1:01:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you eat will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.71,1:01:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday's psychiatric newspaper I'm reading, it says,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.71,1:01:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain antidepressant makes people depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.71,1:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've used it for 20 years and a thousand people.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.00,1:01:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw anybody get depressed on this.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.90,1:01:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What it means is the guy doesn't understand what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.90,1:01:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Prozac went through the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.55,1:01:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It caused people to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.57,1:01:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They misdiagnosed the depression.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.57,1:01:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was actually a bipolar depression.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.57,1:01:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they relieved the depression,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.57,1:01:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the person now had the energy to kill himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.57,1:01:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,To kill an undiagnosed bipolar is to give them an antidepressant.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.17,1:02:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he feels good and he can do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.17,1:02:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But the naivete of the press is unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.75,1:02:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you read the press,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.46,1:02:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to notice something unique that will help you
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.46,1:02:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,undo your fascination with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.55,1:02:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice there's always a writer.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.55,1:02:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever notice that?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.42,1:02:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a story by Ellen Lou Smith,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.53,1:02:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary Jane Peabody, Jack Collier.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.57,1:02:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.76,1:02:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a story written by some yokai.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.76,1:02:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A local who doesn't know anything about the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.57,1:02:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I guarantee that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.19,1:02:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,An article about psychiatry is not written by a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.19,1:02:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's written by Jack Peabody.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.61,1:02:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.61,1:02:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to notice the authority that we give
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.61,1:02:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to what we think is news is nothing but a story.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.34,1:03:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an internet address I could give you,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.34,1:03:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but I forgot it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.34,1:03:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All the media, the articles they want
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.61,1:03:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,on all different kinds of subjects.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.67,1:03:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How to bake a cake, how to kill an Arab,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.86,1:03:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,how to cure your own pneumonia.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.86,1:03:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.11,1:03:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It lists page after page.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.11,1:03:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Articles wanted by all the media out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.11,1:03:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So some joker who's a writer sits down,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.11,1:03:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,he pulls out some data,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.30,1:03:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a little bit of data from here and there,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.30,1:03:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and he quickly writes an article.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.30,1:03:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it becomes the authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.36,1:03:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We live our life imprisoned by fear
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.36,1:03:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,created by the lack of understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.36,1:03:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of writers who don't get the depth and the background
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.36,1:03:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and comprehension of what they're writing about.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.36,1:03:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And it now becomes called truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.36,1:03:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That more people were killed in one passenger car
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.32,1:03:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,than the other means none of us can sit in that seat anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.32,1:03:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, is that a conclusion or what?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.32,1:03:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that stupidity?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.48,1:04:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.19,1:04:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we intellectualize, we mentalize,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.63,1:04:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we idealize, we glamorize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.63,1:04:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we demonize things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.63,1:04:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We get into the chocolate and vanilla problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.63,1:04:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,See, once we redefine these things,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.11,1:04:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see they're not that difficult to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.11,1:04:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you see through the illusion,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.11,1:04:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they're very difficult to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.21,1:04:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Very difficult to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.21,1:04:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see hardly anybody becomes enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.21,1:04:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly anybody even gets to 500, much less enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.21,1:04:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because these are formidable.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.82,1:04:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they look simple to us
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.82,1:04:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when we put them up there and start taking them apart
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.82,1:04:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're like pick-up sticks.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.82,1:04:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you begin to get the sense of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.98,1:04:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all projectile.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.98,1:04:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all projections.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.98,1:04:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all imaginations.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.98,1:04:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all mentations.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.98,1:04:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,None of that exists in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.94,1:04:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to challenge out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.36,1:05:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You can walk up to a tree and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.38,1:05:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how come you look the way you look?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.38,1:05:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.84,1:05:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,People like to argue with consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.84,1:05:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, it's like asking a tree,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.84,1:05:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,why are you what you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.84,1:05:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, it just is that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.92,1:05:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we tend to demonize.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.92,1:05:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the flip side of demonizing
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.92,1:05:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and making everything black and white
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.92,1:05:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is we begin to prize.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.92,1:05:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We prize certain things.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.09,1:05:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So there it brings forth the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.09,1:05:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and its wantingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.09,1:05:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm proud to announce
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.59,1:05:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've given up my desire
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.59,1:05:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for a 1946
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.59,1:05:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Packard converter,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.92,1:05:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Cadillac convertible.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.61,1:05:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid somebody might give me one.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.61,1:05:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The way I got over it was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.57,1:05:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And its caliper went down the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.13,1:06:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want a 46 Lincoln-Continental anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.13,1:06:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, it was sleek.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.53,1:06:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked like 1936 in spades.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.53,1:06:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.53,1:06:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Red on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.36,1:06:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll keep me in the world a while longer.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.80,1:06:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to want something.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.76,1:06:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At the last minute,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.38,1:06:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you think of the Excalibur.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.38,1:06:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing all right
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.15,1:06:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when you just got it down to an Excalibur.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.01,1:06:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we begin to prize.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.01,1:06:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could let that grow.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.01,1:06:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We could let that grow.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.01,1:06:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see how it's just
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.01,1:06:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,even one desire
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.01,1:06:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,could begin to run your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.30,1:06:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to prize certain titles,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.30,1:06:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,certain addresses,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.30,1:06:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,certain lifestyles.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.30,1:06:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes more important
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.46,1:06:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,than anything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.63,1:06:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, success in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.63,1:06:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is what has been prized.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.63,1:07:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.63,1:07:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world in which
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.63,1:07:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,almost all of us grew up,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.63,1:07:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.05,1:07:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,what was prized was success.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.05,1:07:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The college degree,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.05,1:07:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the good address,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.05,1:07:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,all the appurtenances,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.61,1:07:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a reasonably new car.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.61,1:07:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Except, thank you,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.75,1:07:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,younger than 1984.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.19,1:07:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we begin to prize those things,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.23,1:07:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and now they
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.23,1:07:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,run all of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.90,1:07:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one is the greatest
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.90,1:07:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.98,1:07:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.98,1:07:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,fabric of today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.50,1:07:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It is victimized.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.71,1:07:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.75,1:07:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,wondrous suction
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.75,1:07:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that pulls everybody into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.03,1:07:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The great victimization.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.03,1:07:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So these become,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.03,1:07:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all these become tools.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.07,1:07:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Tools of victimization.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.07,1:07:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.13,1:08:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the incredible
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.46,1:08:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,legalities that go on
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.46,1:08:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which can be heard on every night's television.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.46,1:08:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That somebody who
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.55,1:08:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,admittedly was witnessed to drive over
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.55,1:08:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,18 people and kill them all
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.55,1:08:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is innocent because
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.71,1:08:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.14,1:08:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,he's a victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.22,1:08:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the badge of victimhood
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.31,1:08:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is so sought after today.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.31,1:08:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the plushiest,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.51,1:08:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,juiciest plum.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.51,1:08:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can become victim,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.60,1:08:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you got this world by you know what.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.60,1:08:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The race to be victim is
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.81,1:08:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,rapid.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.42,1:08:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone pictures themselves as victim
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.42,1:08:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's great competition
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.42,1:08:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in victimhood
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.42,1:08:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to see who is the biggest victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.67,1:08:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The way the story goes
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.67,1:08:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll see what happens with victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.67,1:08:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A cop's walking down the street
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.22,1:09:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and he hears a rustling.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.22,1:09:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes in and says, young man, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.22,1:09:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The man goes like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.56,1:09:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The cop shoots him.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.56,1:09:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the kid is now the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.57,1:09:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the cop gets sued.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.57,1:09:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.57,1:09:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in the meantime,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.47,1:09:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the kid gets drunk and kills somebody else
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.47,1:09:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,who is now the victim
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.10,1:09:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and goes to court.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.10,1:09:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The witness now becomes the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.67,1:09:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the victim?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.67,1:09:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it's like a ball bouncing around.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.67,1:09:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever it hits is now the next victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.73,1:09:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim of the judiciary,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.77,1:09:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the victim of the perjury.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.77,1:09:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.07,1:09:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The 9-11 bombers are victims.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.07,1:09:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure if they hadn't died
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.07,1:09:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there'd be parades of lawyers
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.07,1:09:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about how their civil rights
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.07,1:09:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are being violated.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.07,1:09:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind 3,000 people
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.07,1:09:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,blown out of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.07,1:10:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So the game of victim now,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.07,1:10:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody gets to be victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.07,1:10:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Every legal situation,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.18,1:10:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,every political situation
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.23,1:10:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is a trade-off on
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.23,1:10:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,who is the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.68,1:10:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the victim?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.61,1:10:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That comes right out of politicizing,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.61,1:10:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,moralizing, idealizing,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.61,1:10:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothesizing, criticizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.61,1:10:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of all of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.84,1:10:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So victimization now
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.84,1:10:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is the world's
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.84,1:10:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,biggest problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.38,1:10:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is the victim
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.38,1:10:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.38,1:10:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the victim of not being
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.38,1:10:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,6'4".
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.38,1:10:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is the victim
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.38,1:10:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of something.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.59,1:10:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The adjective now
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.59,1:10:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,describes the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.60,1:10:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The refinement now is
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.60,1:10:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot mention a person's age.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.60,1:10:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a book out about it in fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.60,1:10:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A new book about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.60,1:10:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth police
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.60,1:11:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.60,1:11:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you can't mention age
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.60,1:11:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because somebody is going to feel victimized
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.60,1:11:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's going to make them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.92,1:11:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Victimization and being uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.92,1:11:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,go hand in hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.18,1:11:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything makes you uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.43,1:11:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't mention gender.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.43,1:11:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't mention any physical data.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.43,1:11:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't mention any
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.43,1:11:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,data of any kind
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.77,1:11:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because that might make people uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.77,1:11:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're bald, you're not bald.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.50,1:11:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That can make you uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.50,1:11:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't say a middle-aged bald man
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.50,1:11:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because you would feel uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.50,1:11:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,if you called a middle-aged bald.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.50,1:11:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The gender police
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.56,1:11:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,would be after you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.75,1:11:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be a middle-aged
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.75,1:11:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you were going to say a man or woman
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.75,1:11:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can't, person.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.75,1:11:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday on the news
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.14,1:11:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we talked about a waiting person.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.14,1:11:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to be a waitress.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.46,1:11:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Honkers or hooters.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.46,1:11:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.46,1:12:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you don't dare
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.46,1:12:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,refer to him as a waitress.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.46,1:12:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wait person.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.82,1:12:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't have a gender
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.82,1:12:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't mention a gender.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.59,1:12:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wait person.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.97,1:12:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.97,1:12:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,everything makes you uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.69,1:12:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is the position of actually paranoia.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.69,1:12:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So what all this
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.69,1:12:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,really leads to
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.69,1:12:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is the prevailing
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.69,1:12:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,paranoia of today's society
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.11,1:12:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you can't make a move.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.11,1:12:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The conversations back and forth
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.46,1:12:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with the hospital
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.46,1:12:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and with the admitting doctor there
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.46,1:12:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,were endless.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.46,1:12:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them was a move
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.02,1:12:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,about whether we were
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.02,1:13:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,going with regulations,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.02,1:13:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,requirements,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.02,1:13:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,whether this was all being documented.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.06,1:13:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to keep carefully
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.06,1:13:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the time they called me,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.06,1:13:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the time they called me back.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.06,1:13:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I called them back
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.06,1:13:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to say the doctor didn't call me back.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.31,1:13:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He called me to tell me
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.31,1:13:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he tried to call me back
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.31,1:13:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but the phone was busy.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.97,1:13:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to document that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.93,1:13:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it sound in court?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.93,1:13:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Neglect.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.92,1:13:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't get him,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.07,1:13:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he couldn't get me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.46,1:13:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody is going to be the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.46,1:13:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the victim industry
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.32,1:13:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,drives our economy right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.32,1:13:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Politically, war, politicians,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.32,1:13:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody is into the victim game.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.32,1:13:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the American public
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.42,1:13:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the victim of George?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.42,1:13:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,George's distortions
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.64,1:13:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.96,1:13:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they want to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.96,1:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Saddam the victim
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.96,1:14:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of these horrible Americans?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.60,1:14:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Are Americans the evil Satan?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.60,1:14:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they are, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.85,1:14:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They drive cars and we don't
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.85,1:14:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so we hate them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.53,1:14:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody who is nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.53,1:14:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in a nowhere country
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.53,1:14:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,still living the Stone Age,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.53,1:14:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to go from nobody to somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.18,1:14:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To go from nobody to somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.68,1:14:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the victim?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.81,1:14:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,His innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.93,1:14:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the basic nature
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.93,1:14:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of human nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.06,1:14:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind intrinsically,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.06,1:14:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the hardware of the mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.18,1:14:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.18,1:14:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is unable to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.80,1:14:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the programming coming in,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.80,1:14:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which we call the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.02,1:14:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.69,1:14:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that because of the intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.69,1:14:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,innocence of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.69,1:14:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.69,1:14:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.69,1:15:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, Krishna,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.69,1:15:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and every great teacher that ever lived
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.69,1:15:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,said, forgive them for they know
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.69,1:15:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not what they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.69,1:15:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The one sin and the one sin only,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.69,1:15:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha said, is that of ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.36,1:15:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,However, don't you see that ignorance
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.11,1:15:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is inborn?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.11,1:15:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're born with the incapacity
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.11,1:15:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to know truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.50,1:15:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the most devastating fact
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.50,1:15:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of human history.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.72,1:15:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Morally responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.72,1:15:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,for every decision,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.97,1:15:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.56,1:15:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.85,1:15:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with no compass
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.85,1:15:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to know what direction to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.69,1:15:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This throws mankind into
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.69,1:15:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,an extreme situation
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.22,1:15:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where he can only hope
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.22,1:15:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which he's been taught
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.22,1:15:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is somewhat near the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.22,1:15:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the likelihood is slim.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.89,1:15:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The likelihood is slim.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.93,1:16:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do what I usually do
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.93,1:16:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is number two.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.93,1:16:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the wise then
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.93,1:16:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,wise up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.51,1:16:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.40,1:16:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the world's population again.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.40,1:16:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to get a different view
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.40,1:16:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as spiritual students,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.40,1:16:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as devotees,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.40,1:16:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever we want to designate ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.76,1:16:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the nature of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.76,1:16:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is the nature of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.76,1:16:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's the relationship between
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.76,1:16:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego and how it sees and experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.76,1:16:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.36,1:16:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have a human population
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.36,1:16:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which over
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.75,1:16:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of thousands of years
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.75,1:16:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,still can't even tell truth
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.75,1:16:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.32,1:16:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even on the first rung
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.32,1:16:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ladder,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.67,1:16:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,despite that profound ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.67,1:16:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.53,1:16:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.53,1:16:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is still in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.53,1:16:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.53,1:17:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,has not reached the level
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.53,1:17:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,where even to know truth from
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.53,1:17:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood would be valued.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.53,1:17:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that phenomenal?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.68,1:17:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, it isn't fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.01,1:17:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are suffering the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.01,1:17:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic consequences of their ignorance
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.01,1:17:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and shouldn't we tell them
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.26,1:17:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,about that, etc.?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.42,1:17:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what, they're not interested.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.42,1:17:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go into the inner city
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.56,1:17:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and talk to the gang kids and tell them
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.56,1:17:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,this way is integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.72,1:17:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and this way is not, they'll say,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.77,1:17:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.73,1:17:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,good luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.73,1:17:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.93,1:17:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But I gotta stay alive, if you don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.93,1:17:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I don't join the gang
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.73,1:17:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I don't do what they do,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.73,1:17:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,if I lose my rank
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.85,1:17:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or respect for me,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.02,1:17:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna get eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.38,1:17:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's very good to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.38,1:17:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,pontificate about
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.47,1:18:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,how they should be,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.23,1:18:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,moralize about it, idealize about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.23,1:18:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we look at the evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.93,1:18:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.93,1:18:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At the present time,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.00,1:18:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.00,1:18:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,only 20 some odd percent
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.00,1:18:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is capable
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.15,1:18:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of discerning truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.15,1:18:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if they had a mechanism
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.15,1:18:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.82,1:18:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest don't even care about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.82,1:18:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's put that previous one back on.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.82,1:18:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What do the rest care about?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.31,1:18:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,People of integrity are excited.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.31,1:18:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, wow, there's a way of telling truth
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.31,1:18:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,from falsehood and even calibrating it?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.31,1:18:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people get so excited
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.81,1:18:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they can't eat for a week,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.10,1:18:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,when I read that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.10,1:18:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.38,1:18:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the mechanisms.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.38,1:18:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do the 78 percent live?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.38,1:18:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do they live?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.81,1:18:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They live because politicized,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.81,1:18:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,moralized and idealized,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.81,1:18:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things create hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.81,1:19:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They create greed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.39,1:19:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They create depression.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.39,1:19:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They create conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.88,1:19:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's where the lives are lived.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.27,1:19:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say to them,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.53,1:19:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got a way to discern
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.53,1:19:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.56,1:19:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity from non-integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.56,1:19:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.56,1:19:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they try to figure out,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.07,1:19:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,well, where can we sell it?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.64,1:19:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Got a new product to move, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.64,1:19:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move this new product, called
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.64,1:19:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the diggity.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.60,1:19:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the thing that's out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.60,1:19:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move this new product.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.65,1:19:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we should take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.32,1:19:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a tough morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.39,1:20:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.93,1:20:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd like to see the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.93,1:20:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we take his picture?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.93,1:20:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.18,1:20:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.09,1:20:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we saw this morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.09,1:20:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,78 percent of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.09,1:20:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.09,1:20:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The first characteristic,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.82,1:21:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I know another dog
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.89,1:21:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.89,1:21:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.02,1:21:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the difference?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.02,1:21:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another dog
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.06,1:21:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates also at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.06,1:21:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Its tail wags.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.60,1:21:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It just loves people.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.60,1:21:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wants something from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.60,1:21:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes up to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.69,1:21:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wants you to acknowledge it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.69,1:21:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice this dog doesn't want anything from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.10,1:21:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that's the difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.10,1:21:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to get attention,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.61,1:21:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,he merely, if I look at him
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.61,1:21:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell him he's a wonderful dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.61,1:21:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he wags his tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.13,1:21:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't want anything from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.13,1:21:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not trying to control me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.14,1:21:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, he doesn't care what we think about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.13,1:21:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.13,1:22:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal is,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.47,1:22:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,he takes his joy from his own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.47,1:22:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the interactions
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.67,1:22:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,add to the joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.67,1:22:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't need my attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.73,1:22:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, as many a dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.73,1:22:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he will run up to you, he's wagging.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.98,1:22:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But he wants your attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.98,1:22:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't want anything from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.56,1:22:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He just ignores me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.39,1:22:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I think you're a sweetheart,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.39,1:22:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and we thank you for coming up.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.65,1:22:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for letting us meet the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.21,1:22:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the joy comes from
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.21,1:22:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,one's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.39,1:22:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And without all
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.73,1:22:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the puzzling things going on
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.73,1:22:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,mentally that afflict humans,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.73,1:22:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he's free to just
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.97,1:22:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy his own
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.80,1:22:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.09,1:23:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the source of joy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.09,1:23:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as we become more and more enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.34,1:23:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That we begin to sense
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.34,1:23:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that the source of joy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.63,1:23:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is our existence in this moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.63,1:23:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just this moment
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.63,1:23:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.63,1:23:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sufficient unto itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.81,1:23:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So one gets outside
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.81,1:23:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the time dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.81,1:23:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because subjectivity
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.81,1:23:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,does not live within the dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.81,1:23:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of time. It just
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.19,1:23:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.61,1:23:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So we remember Ramana Maharshi says,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.61,1:23:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in trying
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.47,1:23:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to change the world, because the world
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.47,1:23:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that you see doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.47,1:23:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rejection
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.47,1:23:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own perceptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.34,1:23:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no one to save.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.32,1:23:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And people are always, we're affronted by that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.32,1:23:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they thought we should
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.32,1:23:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,be doing something.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.32,1:23:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these illusory
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.32,1:23:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,mental states drive
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.32,1:23:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,people into doing things.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.32,1:24:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing things about what they
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.32,1:24:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,imagine is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.27,1:24:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In a forest where a lot of the trees
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.27,1:24:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have been killed off by the bark beetle,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.27,1:24:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what should you do with this
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.52,1:24:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,vast forest with these dead trees?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.52,1:24:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So some people say, well
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.35,1:24:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we must do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.35,1:24:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that the tree's dead, we must cut it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.52,1:24:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to cut it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.52,1:24:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's a dead tree in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.55,1:24:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you leave it be. And in 20 or 30 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.55,1:24:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it just falls down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.47,1:24:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.60,1:24:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So when people say that,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.09,1:24:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, how long do you suppose
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.09,1:24:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that forest has been there? 100,000 years or so?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.09,1:24:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody bothered
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.18,1:24:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,cutting down the dead trees
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.69,1:24:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,over 100,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.69,1:24:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we don't need to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.30,1:24:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So man is always interjecting himself
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.30,1:24:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in nature and trying to improve
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.30,1:24:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on that which does not need improvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.30,1:25:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,To really see that,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.14,1:25:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,though, means to be totally
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.14,1:25:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,accepting, totally accepting.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.14,1:25:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I thought we'd talk a little bit
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.11,1:25:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,about the field
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.27,1:25:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.27,1:25:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I thought we'd do something
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.65,1:25:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we did someplace recently
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.65,1:25:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we talked.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.81,1:25:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of questions and answers coming up
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.81,1:25:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by cards, although we do have cards,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.81,1:25:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or a microphone traveling around
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.81,1:25:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the audience, we found that was not satisfactory,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.81,1:25:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we had people just come up
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.89,1:25:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and we started discussing
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.89,1:25:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.07,1:25:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought today we'll try that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.18,1:25:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to present a few things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.18,1:25:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought people that want to talk
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.18,1:25:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to me, why don't you come up
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.18,1:25:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and talk to me. We'll ask questions
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.18,1:25:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and discuss things as a small group,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.18,1:25:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but the whole audience will hear the discussion.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.18,1:25:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.18,1:25:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because many people have questions,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.18,1:25:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't read
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.30,1:26:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so well, so a 3x5 card,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.30,1:26:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if somebody just tells me
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.77,1:26:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is that's on their mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.77,1:26:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because an interview
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.80,1:26:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is artificial. Somebody has written down
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.80,1:26:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,questions, but that's not really
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.80,1:26:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what's bothering them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.80,1:26:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I like is the authenticity
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.80,1:26:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of the one-to-one
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.02,1:26:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,people asking a question, because that is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.02,1:26:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a real question to them. It's a real question,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.02,1:26:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not something that was written down by an editor.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.02,1:26:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore they get a real answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.06,1:26:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we did that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.11,1:26:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at Mile High. We didn't know that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.11,1:26:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the microphone was on, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.11,1:26:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And people were coming up with these questions,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.11,1:26:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course I'm just being my real self,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.11,1:26:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.11,1:26:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She's
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.11,1:26:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,lamenting the illness of her daughter,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.11,1:26:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm telling her, well, you should go to a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.11,1:26:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,12-step group, you should go to Elman
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.11,1:26:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or something. She says, I've been going for 12 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.11,1:26:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, because there was nobody witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.11,1:26:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this, I thought, I said, well, for God's sake,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.11,1:26:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't you take the first step?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.11,1:26:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm shaking her, it's about time to take
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.11,1:27:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the first step after 12 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.11,1:27:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she went into shock, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.11,1:27:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.14,1:27:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,my natural state is more like Zen
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.14,1:27:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,than a Christian saint,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.14,1:27:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you know. And then after
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.22,1:27:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,this is all over, all these people came up
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.22,1:27:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.22,1:27:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a go-around with everybody, and the group was all
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.22,1:27:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,involved, and everybody was listening, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.22,1:27:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when it was over, we found
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.22,1:27:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the hall was full of people sitting there
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.22,1:27:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,just fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.22,1:27:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They were, you know, right in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.22,1:27:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,these conversations, and we didn't even know
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.22,1:27:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,this was on, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.48,1:27:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But then I thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.10,1:27:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, maybe that's a good thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.10,1:27:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't tried it with this audience, so maybe we should
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.10,1:27:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.10,1:27:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so first I'll explain
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.10,1:27:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a few other things I always want to clarify,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.10,1:27:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I thought, well, people
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.47,1:27:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,will ask us real questions. We'll start
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.47,1:27:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with the ones that we...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.02,1:28:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh, real good one, uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.77,1:28:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.06,1:28:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Betty prompted me, said,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.06,1:28:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you mentioned the 12-step program.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.06,1:28:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people are not familiar with it?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.46,1:28:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so there's more than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.68,1:28:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so prevalent in our society
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.68,1:28:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that almost everybody has a relative,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.68,1:28:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a friend, a fellow employee,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.71,1:28:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,their boss, or somebody,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.71,1:28:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the 12-step idea,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.28,1:28:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, came out of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.28,1:28:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the Oxford Groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.35,1:28:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The Oxford Groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.35,1:28:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And, um,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.40,1:28:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the Oxford Groups lived by
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.40,1:28:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain set of spiritual principles.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.40,1:28:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just a spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.50,1:28:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.50,1:28:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It consisted of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.76,1:28:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the Oxford principles,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.76,1:28:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there was only six, not 12,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.76,1:28:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and it had nothing to do with alcoholism.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.76,1:28:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But when Roland, who was
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.07,1:28:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a hopeless alcoholic,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.52,1:28:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,went to see Carl Jung in Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.52,1:28:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung was, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.52,1:29:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a very great and famous psychoanalyst.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.52,1:29:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And after seeing Jung
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.75,1:29:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for some time, he moved to Switzerland
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.75,1:29:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to be in psychoanalysis
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.75,1:29:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jung.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.48,1:29:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And he became sober.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.48,1:29:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So Roland went back to New York City
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.48,1:29:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and within a short time
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.55,1:29:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,was drunk again.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.55,1:29:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Roland went back
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.81,1:29:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to Switzerland
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.81,1:29:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to see Carl Jung.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.81,1:29:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do now?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.81,1:29:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,His great hope was Carl Jung
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.06,1:29:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and his psychoanalysis,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.06,1:29:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and now he had collapsed again.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.06,1:29:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the depths of depression,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.06,1:29:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he pleaded with Carl Jung.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.31,1:29:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung, to whom we are all grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.31,1:29:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to this day,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.60,1:29:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he calibrated 520.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.60,1:29:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Carl Jung said,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.11,1:29:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,he was honest, he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.11,1:29:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,alas, alas, he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.11,1:29:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,neither my science nor my art
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.34,1:29:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,can help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.34,1:29:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it has been recorded,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.81,1:29:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,rarely, but it has been recorded
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.81,1:29:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by people who have recovered
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.81,1:30:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by throwing themselves wholeheartedly
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.81,1:30:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,into a spiritual group.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.18,1:30:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So Roland went back to the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.18,1:30:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,very dejected and very depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.18,1:30:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I guess he was
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.36,1:30:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,not a very spiritual person.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.36,1:30:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he threw himself in
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.36,1:30:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,wholeheartedly into the Oxford groups
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.36,1:30:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and lo and behold, Roland became sober.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.36,1:30:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Roland passed this on to
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.35,1:30:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Evie, who came to Bill W.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.35,1:30:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And Bill W
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.39,1:30:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,was in the same state of despair
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.39,1:30:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and they told him
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.42,1:30:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that only by turning himself over to God
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.42,1:30:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,could he have any chance of hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.42,1:30:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Bill was an atheist
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.42,1:30:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time, so it didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.42,1:30:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,appeal to him too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.46,1:30:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But also, at death's door,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.46,1:30:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill W did surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.46,1:30:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the ego to God
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.46,1:30:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the room lit up
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.46,1:30:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with a great light.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.97,1:30:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And he went through
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.94,1:31:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a profound transformation
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.59,1:31:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which arose all the 12 step
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.59,1:31:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,recovery groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.90,1:31:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of that one moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.90,1:31:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the room lit up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.90,1:31:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that, millions
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.90,1:31:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of people have recovered
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.90,1:31:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from all kinds of diseases
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.06,1:31:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,by following these 12 basic steps.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.06,1:31:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The first demonstration
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.57,1:31:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of this efficacy
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.57,1:31:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was in the curing of alcoholism,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.57,1:31:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which many people here don't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.57,1:31:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because in the modern era
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.57,1:31:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's considered to be recoverable.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.57,1:31:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the old days, it was a sentence of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.71,1:31:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody recovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.71,1:31:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You died of a wet brain
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.64,1:31:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because of insanity and convulsions.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.64,1:31:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was witnessed
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.80,1:31:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by everybody around
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.80,1:31:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the miraculous recovery
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.80,1:31:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from a hopeless progressive disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.80,1:31:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the word spread
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.43,1:31:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and AA grew
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.43,1:31:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course it now is worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.43,1:31:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if these 12 steps
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.43,1:31:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,could bring about recovery
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.43,1:32:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,from hopeless progressive diseases
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.43,1:32:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for which there was no cure
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.43,1:32:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because medicine, psychiatry
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.43,1:32:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and psychology have no cure for it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.43,1:32:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and neither does religion,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.43,1:32:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Catholic priests
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.76,1:32:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who have an alcoholism rate
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.76,1:32:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of 10 or 15 percent
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.76,1:32:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to get sober and go to AA.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.76,1:32:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So there was something about
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.07,1:32:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12 steps then
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.07,1:32:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,had great power.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.07,1:32:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,People began to apply this
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.23,1:32:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to other illnesses
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.23,1:32:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and so now the 12 step recovery
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.23,1:32:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,principles
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.27,1:32:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrated 540
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.27,1:32:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are applied
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.36,1:32:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to many of life's intractable problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.36,1:32:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Drug addiction,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.36,1:32:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,alcoholism,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.17,1:32:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,drug addiction and loss
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.17,1:32:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and people who are prone to violence
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.17,1:32:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and anger and rage
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.17,1:32:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and all kinds of victimhood
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.19,1:32:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and spending people
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.19,1:32:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are compulsive spenders etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.19,1:32:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of things
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.42,1:32:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for which there really is no cure
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.42,1:33:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,hopeless illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.42,1:33:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was found then
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.42,1:33:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that the energy fuel
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.42,1:33:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates at 540
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.42,1:33:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,had the capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.42,1:33:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if you did the steps,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.64,1:33:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore I have a great interest in it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.64,1:33:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,aside from alcoholism
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.64,1:33:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,just the 12 steps themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.86,1:33:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,much as I have an interest
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.86,1:33:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.86,1:33:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.86,1:33:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the course of which
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.86,1:33:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen recovery from
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.89,1:33:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,endless numbers
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.06,1:33:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of hopeless diseases
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.06,1:33:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from multiple sclerosis
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.06,1:33:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to myasthenia gravis
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.15,1:33:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to all kinds of incurables.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.15,1:33:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know that spiritual power
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.15,1:33:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then has the capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.15,1:33:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's karmically okay to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.15,1:33:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman called me
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.51,1:33:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd seen and she said
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.51,1:33:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.60,1:33:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through a spiritual transformation
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.98,1:33:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and she said
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.18,1:33:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the cancer of the breast had disappeared
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.18,1:33:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,she called me up to tell me
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.18,1:34:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the x-ray showed
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.18,1:34:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it was now gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.34,1:34:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather everyday occurrences
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.34,1:34:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,within the power of the spiritual field
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.34,1:34:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,anything may recover
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.34,1:34:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you do
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.35,1:34:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12 steps
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.35,1:34:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or you do the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.35,1:34:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,thoroughly
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.46,1:34:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't matter whether you recover or not
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.46,1:34:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because recovery
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.46,1:34:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is trying to control God
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.46,1:34:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,once you surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.46,1:34:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if this is the way you're going to go
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.46,1:34:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,then this is the way you're going to go
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.21,1:34:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so let's look at the 12 steps
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.88,1:34:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who are not familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.06,1:34:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend the 12 steps
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.06,1:34:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to anybody in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.06,1:34:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for anything
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.64,1:34:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is merely
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.64,1:34:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual way of living.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.64,1:34:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Oxford groups
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.86,1:34:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the Oxford groups were not religious
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.86,1:34:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they said what is the spiritual core
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.86,1:34:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the spiritual core of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.86,1:34:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because they were disillusioned
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.97,1:35:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with traditional religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.97,1:35:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.02,1:35:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we admit we are powerless
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.02,1:35:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and in our case
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.02,1:35:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as seekers of enlightenment over the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.02,1:35:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and that our lives have become unmanageable
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.02,1:35:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.50,1:35:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,my life is unmanageable
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.56,1:35:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,my life is not unmanageable
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.56,1:35:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say well let's see
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.56,1:35:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,let's stop your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.56,1:35:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from thinking for a second
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.56,1:35:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't think it was unmanageable
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.56,1:35:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you just learned in one second
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.56,1:35:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that it goes right on
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.72,1:35:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it thumbs its nose at you
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.72,1:35:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind and your ego
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.72,1:35:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,thumb their nose at you
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.10,1:35:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell it not to do this
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.10,1:35:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will promptly do that
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.10,1:35:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,do not forget to put the butter
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.10,1:35:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the refrigerator
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.10,1:35:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you get home from the movie
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.10,1:35:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cat's been licking it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.10,1:35:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,while you were gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.10,1:35:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and you want to
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.10,1:35:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,change the world
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.10,1:35:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they want to change
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.30,1:36:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all these people want to change the world
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.30,1:36:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,can't remember to tie their shoelaces
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.02,1:36:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,ok so first is the surrender of humility
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.02,1:36:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so the secret of success
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.02,1:36:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.02,1:36:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or this spiritual pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.02,1:36:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or devotional non-duality
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.02,1:36:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is humility
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.05,1:36:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize the profound limitation
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.05,1:36:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.07,1:36:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the great difficulty
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.07,1:36:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the slightest thing
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.88,1:36:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore when we looked at ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.88,1:36:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,honestly
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.88,1:36:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so the first step is one of honesty
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.88,1:36:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,people that are in hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.30,1:36:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and down below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.86,1:36:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,step one takes you to
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.86,1:36:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity right away
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.34,1:36:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,step one you're honest with yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.34,1:36:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,left to my own devices
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.34,1:36:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,there's really nothing I can do about this
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.34,1:36:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,condition therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.53,1:36:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,through experience
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.65,1:36:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say through experience
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.65,1:36:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but it says came to believe
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.65,1:37:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that a power greater than ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.65,1:37:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,could restore us to sanity
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.90,1:37:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,sanity doesn't mean lying in bed
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.38,1:37:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,worrying about everything
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.38,1:37:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean trying to anticipate
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.38,1:37:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow's disasters
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.38,1:37:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't mean ruminating
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.38,1:37:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,about the wrongs of the past
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.38,1:37:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it means
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.89,1:37:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,people don't know what sanity is
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.23,1:37:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind itself is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.55,1:37:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,still
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.61,1:37:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it says nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.65,1:37:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say anything to you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.53,1:37:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to think God is talking to you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.53,1:37:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,something is talking to you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.68,1:37:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,space doesn't talk to you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.77,1:37:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but in space
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.06,1:37:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a knowingness begins to arise
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.06,1:37:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it arises
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.06,1:37:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the outer fields of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.06,1:37:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,through the knowing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.06,1:38:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a knowingness of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.06,1:38:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes about through the knowingness of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.06,1:38:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if God spoke to you
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.47,1:38:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it would turn you into a cinder
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.47,1:38:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in a second
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.47,1:38:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,if an archangel even hears a prayer
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.02,1:38:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and passes a thought to you
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.02,1:38:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it would blow you out for 30 years
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.73,1:38:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,stunned into silence
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.73,1:38:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind never speaks again
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.73,1:38:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and if God thought of you
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.92,1:38:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,holy catfish
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.61,1:38:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,came to believe that a power greater than ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.61,1:38:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,could restore us to sanity
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.93,1:38:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,step three
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.93,1:38:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we made a decision to turn our will
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.93,1:38:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and our lives over to the care of God
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.93,1:38:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as we understood them
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.22,1:38:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,turn our will
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.81,1:38:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and our lives over to God
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.81,1:38:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.14,1:38:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the crux of this
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.14,1:38:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is the profound humility
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.43,1:38:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it means no matter what
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.43,1:38:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the no matter whatness
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.93,1:39:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,arises again just as you break through
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.93,1:39:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,into the state of enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.39,1:39:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.73,1:39:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,one gets at the last door
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.73,1:39:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that one
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.06,1:39:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is expected or needs to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.06,1:39:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or the field
