Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.84,1:47:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,step six is another one
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.77,1:47:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.77,1:47:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we're entirely ready
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.77,1:47:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to have God remove
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.77,1:47:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all these defects of character
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.53,1:47:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,have God remove these
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.53,1:47:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so we surrender them to God
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.53,1:47:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so all the things we did on the list
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.53,1:47:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.53,1:47:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,dear God I really need help
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.53,1:47:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,criticalness
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.81,1:47:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,my constantly politicizing everything
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.81,1:47:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,idealizing everything
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.81,1:47:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,moralizing about everything
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.81,1:47:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,can't anything happen in this world
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.59,1:47:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,without my having an opinion on it
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.89,1:47:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,do I have to keep hating chocolate
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.89,1:47:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or can I just let chocolate
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.89,1:47:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,be chocolate and say
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.89,1:48:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I prefer vanilla
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.02,1:48:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,ok so if politics
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.02,1:48:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was cheering on your favorite
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.02,1:48:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,championing a belief system
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.02,1:48:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be great but it tends to take on
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.02,1:48:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,attacking chocolate
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.02,1:48:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,alright
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.02,1:48:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to take personal inventory
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.02,1:48:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we asked him
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.22,1:48:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to remove our shortcomings
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.22,1:48:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see that's the essence of it
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.22,1:48:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now one could use
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.22,1:48:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a mechanism you ask God to remove
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.22,1:48:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,your shortcomings
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.42,1:48:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next thing your mother says to you
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.42,1:48:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is maybe you ought to see
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.42,1:48:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.69,1:48:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how God wants you to remove
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.69,1:48:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that shortcoming
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.69,1:48:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mechanism here the psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.69,1:48:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,he's only the mechanism
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.53,1:48:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,when you ask God for help
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.65,1:48:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with something and a guy
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.65,1:48:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,screeches up to you and says
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.65,1:48:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you got a flat tire can I help
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.65,1:48:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean that isn't God but
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.65,1:48:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had it happen in the middle of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.65,1:48:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,completely deserted
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.92,1:48:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and a guy pulls up next to me
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.92,1:49:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,he says you got problems
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.92,1:49:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the tire is flat
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.07,1:49:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he puts it on his truck
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.07,1:49:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he drives it into his town
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.59,1:49:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,gets it fixed brings it back to me
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.68,1:49:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and helps me put it on
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.46,1:49:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,humbly ask God to remove our shortcomings
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.46,1:49:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and God may suggest a mechanism
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.46,1:49:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you need Prozac
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.46,1:49:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,well of course
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.18,1:49:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the miracle says physical mental and spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.18,1:49:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and AA and the 12 step group
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.18,1:49:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,say physical mental and spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.18,1:49:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if you really want to stop being depressed
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.18,1:49:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,then you wouldn't be resistant
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.18,1:49:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,about taking an antidepressant
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.18,1:49:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if you really wanted to be undepressed
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.18,1:49:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,then you would take an antidepressant wouldn't you
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.18,1:49:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the very fact that you don't want to take it
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.18,1:49:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,means that you're getting juice out of being depressed
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.18,1:49:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,getting to be the sick victim
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.18,1:49:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the old poor me
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.34,1:49:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,okay so resistance
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.34,1:49:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so each step brings up resistance
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.38,1:49:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,next to undo the guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:49:53.38,1:49:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we made a list of all the persons we harmed
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.38,1:49:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and became willing to make amends to them all
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.81,1:49:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say in that step that you do
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.81,1:50:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say you write your boss yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.75,1:50:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it says you became willing
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.75,1:50:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.75,1:50:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness on our calibrated chart
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.75,1:50:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the high 300's
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.75,1:50:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.88,1:50:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as you do the steps it's automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.88,1:50:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,going to take you up the calibrated scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.88,1:50:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,into humility
Dialogue: 0,1:50:20.88,1:50:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,into willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.93,1:50:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so we became willing
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.93,1:50:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to make amends to them all
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.93,1:50:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then where possible
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.32,1:50:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we made direct amends whenever possible
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.32,1:50:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,except when
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.32,1:50:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to do them would create scandal
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.32,1:50:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,injure them
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.97,1:50:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or others
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.22,1:50:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there's some things that to reveal it
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.22,1:50:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,would be so disturbing to people
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.22,1:50:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that out of compassion for them
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.22,1:50:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,then out of compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.22,1:50:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for them
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.35,1:50:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so this is another reason to have a counselor
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.35,1:50:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or a confessor
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.93,1:50:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or a priest or a doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.93,1:50:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrist psychologist therapist
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.93,1:51:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,good friend
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.72,1:51:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,one's parents can sometimes
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.72,1:51:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,under unusual circumstances
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.72,1:51:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,even one's spouse
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.72,1:51:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you can admit to a spouse
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.81,1:51:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I did such and such
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.81,1:51:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and I sure wish I hadn't
Dialogue: 0,1:51:13.81,1:51:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and if there's real love there
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.81,1:51:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so a true relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.81,1:51:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're aligned
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.81,1:51:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,with one as therapeutically
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.81,1:51:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and loving as possible
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.81,1:51:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so people who have a good relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.81,1:51:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or a good marriage relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.81,1:51:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or a very good friend
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.92,1:51:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you can reveal almost anything
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.92,1:51:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will try to recontextualize it
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.92,1:51:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see it differently
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.10,1:51:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work is considerably
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.10,1:51:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,as you know by now
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.10,1:51:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualizing a thing
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.10,1:51:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so what you thought was the worst thing in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.30,1:51:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,when recontextualized
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.30,1:51:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize is due to the weakness of human nature
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.30,1:51:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,including your own
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.50,1:51:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the weakness of human nature
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.61,1:51:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the limitation of human nature
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.61,1:51:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is what accounts for most of the things
Dialogue: 0,1:51:56.61,1:51:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we shake our heads over
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.64,1:52:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so we tried to make amends to people
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.64,1:52:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,when we could
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.64,1:52:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,except when to do so
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.64,1:52:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would injure them or others
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.44,1:52:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so that precludes dumping
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.44,1:52:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because you feel guilty about
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.44,1:52:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the affair you had 32 years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.44,1:52:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to blow your wife away now
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.44,1:52:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell her about that night
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.44,1:52:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you got drunk in Chicago
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.18,1:52:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean you wish it hadn't happened
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.18,1:52:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,agonizing you for 32 years with guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.18,1:52:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but to dump it on her
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.88,1:52:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is dumping
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.88,1:52:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's misusing her
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.88,1:52:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to hurt her
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.88,1:52:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it doesn't really mean anything
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.17,1:52:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's better to discuss
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.19,1:52:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with a confessor
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.19,1:52:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,should I bring this up
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.19,1:52:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what's your purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.19,1:52:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,just so you don't feel so guilty
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.19,1:52:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,well good for you but what about her
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.19,1:52:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so you have to look at the consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.19,1:52:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and avoid
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.19,1:52:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,dumping your stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.19,1:52:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on others
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.10,1:53:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we made direct amends
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.10,1:53:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,then step 10 is what
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.10,1:53:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,makes this different from many others
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.10,1:53:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we continue to take personal inventory
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.10,1:53:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on a daily basis
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.10,1:53:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we were wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.10,1:53:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,promptly admitted it
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.98,1:53:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just think of poor old Nixon
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.98,1:53:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.98,1:53:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that have gone down the tubes
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.98,1:53:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that if they told the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.27,1:53:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and admitted it right at the beginning
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.27,1:53:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody said well I was pretty dumb
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.27,1:53:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but so
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.88,1:53:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,promptly admitted it
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.10,1:53:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so we don't have to walk around
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.10,1:53:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.35,1:53:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because when we were wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:53:37.35,1:53:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we promptly admitted
Dialogue: 0,1:53:40.13,1:53:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and couples do that all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.13,1:53:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I snapped at you
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.13,1:53:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I forgot to bring home the butter
Dialogue: 0,1:53:46.38,1:53:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.38,1:53:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,people apologize for
Dialogue: 0,1:53:50.77,1:53:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,character logic problems
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.09,1:53:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's consideration of others
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.31,1:53:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we continue to take personal inventory
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.31,1:53:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we were wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.31,1:54:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,promptly admitted it
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.34,1:54:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,just think of poor old Nixon
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.34,1:54:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.34,1:54:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that have gone down the tubes
Dialogue: 0,1:54:07.34,1:54:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to eğ
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.07,1:54:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,thing would have blown away and everybody would have forgiven them so we
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.96,1:54:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,find that in the long term to admit when you're wrong right off the bat is
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.85,1:54:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,actually the best way to go the most practical and certainly politics has
Dialogue: 0,1:54:47.47,1:54:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,proven that over and over again hiding a thing away and sooner or later comes out
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.81,1:54:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and now and now the cost is great can cost you the the office itself and you
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.43,1:55:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,have to resign so instead of a slap on the wrist you have a major catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.07,1:55:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's very practical step 10 also you can stay in integrity step 11 is the
Dialogue: 0,1:55:16.22,1:55:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,backbone of many a person's spiritual work sought through prayer and meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.90,1:55:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to become more conscious we all move towards enlightenment conscious contact
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.00,1:55:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with God as we understood him praying only for his knowledge of his will for
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.00,1:55:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,us
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.30,1:55:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,oh that's different then please God do this and please God do that that's the
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.72,1:55:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,child in us running for the bus with your violin you're gonna be late for
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.39,1:55:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,your violin lesson and you're praying up a storm God please hold the bus I can
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.46,1:56:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,remember that the violin flying through the air and running like a mad dog less
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.00,1:56:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,school late and now it's gonna miss the bus and miss my violin listen dear God
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.93,1:56:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,please hold the bus yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.90,1:56:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so in this we surrender our will to God and we ask for knowledge of his will for
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.82,1:56:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,us so you're asking for spiritual intuition a certain knowingness so
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.67,1:56:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to transcend the ego the ego lives in this box and the ego says
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.47,1:56:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,well I'll figure it out but surrendering it to God is not figuring it out it's
Dialogue: 0,1:56:37.86,1:56:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,not figuring it out at all in fact it may look quite hopeless and a
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.71,1:56:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but we continue in humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:45.84,1:56:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We seek through prayer and meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:47.77,1:56:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And what then happens is it suddenly comes to us
Dialogue: 0,1:56:51.80,1:56:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a recontextualization of what we thought was a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.35,1:56:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we see it wasn't even a problem in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.88,1:57:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you'd gotten that job, you would have gone down
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.06,1:57:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because you didn't know what that company was
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.64,1:57:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in its last few months.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.03,1:57:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And so step 11 then, prayer and meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.60,1:57:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And step 12 is one reason many of us are here.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:18.27,1:57:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Having had a spiritual awakening
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.31,1:57:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of a spiritually integrous life,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.47,1:57:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we tried to carry this message to others
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.18,1:57:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and practice these principles in all our affairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.65,1:57:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So we then began to uplift others
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.18,1:57:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,by sharing our experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.78,1:57:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sharing your experience
Dialogue: 0,1:57:40.18,1:57:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is not trying to change the other person.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.47,1:57:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll tell this person this for their own good.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.80,1:57:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do anything for anybody's own good.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:50.46,1:57:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, say, I went to Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.94,1:57:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw people recover from myasthenia gravis,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.59,1:58:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,cancer, tumors, convulsive disorder.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.94,1:58:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And you leave off, and therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.63,1:58:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you ought to be going.
